asgn2Simulators

Class Simulator

  • java.lang.Object
    • asgn2Simulators.Simulator

  • public class Simulator
extends java.lang.Object
    Class to hold parameters and to provide random trial services for the simulation. Simulation relies by default on parameters set in the file Constants. User has the option to set these parameters using the multi-argument constructor. Methods provide daily booking levels according to the distribution N(meanBookings,sdBookings^2), and outcomes for fare class selection (or passenger creation) and other random decisions.
    Author:
    hogan

        Constructor for Simulator using defaults

      • Simulator

        public Simulator(int seed,
         int maxQueueSize,
         double meanDailyBookings,
         double sdDailyBookings,
         double firstProb,
         double businessProb,
         double premiumProb,
         double economyProb,
         double cancelProb)
          throws SimulationException
        Constructor for simulator allowing setting of all values. Parameters tell the story.
        Parameters:
        seed - int random number generator seed
        maxQueueSize - int holding max permissible queue size
        meanDailyBookings - double holding the mean of the Normal Distribution of daily bookings
        sdDailyBookings - double holding the standard deviation of the booking distribution
        firstProb - double holding the probability that current booking will be First Class
        businessProb - double holding the probability that current booking will be Business Class
        premiumProb - double holding the probability that current booking will be Premium Economy
        economyProb - double holding the probability that current booking will be Economy Class
        cancelProb - double holding the probability of cancellation from confirmedSeat
        Throws:
        SimulationException - if one or more probabilities are invalid, or if meanDailyBookings < 0 or sdDailyBookings < 0

      • randomSuccess

        public static boolean randomSuccess(java.util.Random rng,
                    double successProb)
        Static utility method to implement a Bernoulli Trial, a coin toss with two outcomes: success (probability successProb) and failure (probability 1-successProb)
        Parameters:
        rng - Random generating the random sequence of numbers
        successProb - double holding the success probability
        Returns:
        true if trial was successful, false otherwise

      • createPassenger

        public Passenger createPassenger(int bookingTime,
                        int departureTime)
                          throws PassengerException
        Method to create a New Passenger. Fare class is decided using probabilities set in the constructor. Usually, these will be the values from asgn1Simulators.Constants. We return the appropriate object from the asgn1Passengers.Passenger hierarchy.
        Returns:
        new Passenger of type {First,Business,Premium,Economy} according to RNG
        Throws:
        PassengerException - if invalid constructor parameters. See asgn1Passengers.Passenger#Passenger(int,int)
